  <info>
    <title>Managing logical volumes</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        &cockpit; enables you to administer logical volumes. You can deactivate
        or activate volumes, delete them, or change the size of the volumes.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    To perform any administration task on an existing logical volume,
    perform the following steps:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Navigate to the <guimenu>Storage</guimenu> page.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        In the <guimenu>Filesystems</guimenu> view, click the logical volume.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Here you can perform the following actions with existing logical
        volumes:
      </para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Deactivate/Activate</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              In the three-dots menu select <guimenu>Deactive</guimenu> or
              <guimenu>Activate</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Mount</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              By clicking <guimenu>Mount</guimenu> and fill in the mount point
              and options, the volume will be mounted.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Shrink/Grow</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              Bear in mind, that the shrink/grow function is not available for
              all file systems.
            </para>
            <para>
              In the expanded details about the volume, click
              <guimenu>Shrink</guimenu> or <guimenu>Grow</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Delete</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              In the three-dots menu select <guimenu>Delete</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
